    "notes": "Salt-shaped deterministic Bandersnatch variable-base MSM: 256 projective bases and eight repeated scalar vectors. Each timed call performs the same projective-to-affine batch normalization and checked MSM as banderwagon::multi_scalar_mul; deterministic CRS/scalar construction remains outside timing. The differential uses the identical workload, canonical length-delimited serialization and SHA-256, checks checked/unchecked/reference equivalence and rerun determinism, asserts inputs are unchanged, and proves the mutation fingerprint changes. Editable scope is only co-reached variable-base MSM/window selection, twisted-Edwards group operations/normalization, and Bandersnatch curve glue; ark-ff kernels belong to the field lane and are excluded."
